  "text": "• Visual: This is a 1-dimensional vector (saliency map), which can be considered a simple model of retina (same as in [CITATION_1] ). This input consists of 20 units corresponding to 20 spacial locations. Depending on the presence of an object in a given location, each unit of the visual input will be activated or not. The maximal number of objects assumed in presented experiments is 10, their locations are chosen randomly. The visual input is normalized to 1 in order to eliminate possibility of discrimination of cardinality based on summed activation of that input.",
